   Millicom Unit in Bolivia
</HL>
<DATE>
09/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   MILL LATAM
</CO>
<IN>
TELEPHONE SYSTEMS (TLS)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Millicom Inc. said a joint venture, in which
one of its subsidiaries is a shareholder, was awarded a
license to provide cellular-telephone service in Bolivia.
   The license, awarded in a bidding process, is the first
that the Bolivian government has granted, Millicom said. The
system initially will serve the country's major metropolitan
areas. Officials declined to value the transaction.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Millicom, a communications company, said it initially
would hold 46% of the operation. The subsidiary is Millicom
International Holdings Ltd. Comvik International AB, a
Swedish telecommunications concern, will hold 23%; the
group's Bolivian partners, a group of local business people,
will hold 31%.
</TEXT>
