<HL>
   West German Raw Steel Output
</HL>
<DATE>
09/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C12
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   FRANKFURT, West Germany -- Production of raw steel in West
Germany in August fell 12% to 3.1 million metric tons from
3.6 million tons a year earlier, continuing a trend evident
through the year, the Federal Statistics Office said. A
metric ton is equal to about 2,204.62 pounds.
   The August output represented a daily production rate of
108,035 metric tons, down from a daily rate of 122,368 tons a
year earlier. Both months had 29 production days.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In the first eight months of this year, West Germany's
raw-steel production fell 7.7% to 25.7 million metric tons.
   The volume of raw iron produced in August fell 14% from a
year earlier to 2.4 million metric tons. In the first eight
months, iron output declined 9.6% to 20.2 million tons.
</TEXT>
