<IN>
MORTGAGES, MORTGAGE BANKERS, MORTGAGE-BACKED SECURITIES (MOR)
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
</IN>
<LP>
   The following were among yesterday's offerings and
pricings in U.S. and non-U.S. capital markets, with terms and
syndicate manager, as compiled by Dow Jones Capital Markets
Report.
                                                                                                       

                         MUNICIPAL
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   California Housing Finance Agency -- $185 million of home
mortgage revenue bonds, Series D, due Aug. 1, 2010 and 2031,
with capital appreciation bonds due Feb. 1 and Aug. 1,
2000-2004 and Aug. 1, 2020, tentatively priced by a Merrill
Lynch Capital Markets group to yield from 7.40% in 2000 to
8.10% in 2020. There are $31.2 million of 7 3/4% term bonds
priced at par due in 2010 and $129.9 million of 7 7/8% term
bonds priced at par due in 2031. Capital appreciation bonds
are priced to yield from 7.40% in 2000 to 7.75% in 2004.
There is $104.4 million of capital appreciation bonds priced
to yield 8.10% to maturity in 2020. The bonds are rated
double-A/single-A-plus.
   Virginia Housing Development Authority -- $132.9 million
of commonwealth mortgage bonds, 1990 Series A, Subseries
A-STEM, due June 26, 1991, and 1990 Series B, Subseries
BSTEM-II, due April 24, 1991, priced by a First Boston Corp.
group. There are $64.2 million of 6.45% bonds priced at par
due June 26, 1991, and $68.7 million of 6% bonds priced at
par due April 24, 1991. Interest on the Series A bonds will
treated as a preference item in calculating the federal
alternative minimum tax that may be imposed on certain
investors. The Series B bonds are not subject to the
alternative minimum tax. The bonds are rated
V-MIG-1/single-A-1plus.
   New York State Medical Care Facilities Finance Agency --
$114 million of FHA-insured hospital mortgage revenue bonds
for Presbyterian Hospital, priced Wednesday by Merrill Lynch
Capital Markets group. The issue, 1990 Series A, due Feb. 15,
2000, 2009 and 2025, is priced to yield from 7.10% in 2000 to
7.79% in 2025. There are $19.8 million of 7.10% term bonds
priced at par due in 2000, $38.3 million of 7.70% term bonds
priced at 99 3/4 to yield 7.73% in 2009 and $56.1 million of
7.70% term bonds priced at 98 7/8 to yield 7.79% in 2025.
Ratings of double-A/double-A are expected on the issue.
   New York City Industrial Development Agency -- $84 million
of special facility revenue bonds, 1990 American Airlines
Inc. Project, due July 1, 2019 and 2020, tentatively priced
by a Bear Stearns &amp; Co. group to yield 8.06% in 2019 and
8.07% in 2020. There are about $13 million of 7 3/4% term
