of 8% term bonds priced at 99 1/4 to yield 8.07% in 2020.
Interest on the bonds will be treated as a preference item in
calculating the federal alternative minimum tax. The bonds
are rated single-A-3/single-A.
   University Community Hospital Inc. (A Florida Corp. Not
for Profit) -- $81.4 million of revenue and refunding revenue
bonds priced Wednesday by a Merrill Lynch Capital Markets
group. The issue, Series 1990, due Sept. 1, 1992-2002, 2007
and 2011, is priced to yield from 6.10% in 1992 to 7.55% in
2011. Current interest serial bonds are priced at par to
yield from 6.10% in 1992. There are $29.2 million of 7 3/8%
term bonds priced at 99 to yield 7.48% in 2007. There are
$32.2 million of 7 1/2% term bonds priced at 99 1/2 to yield
7.55% in 2011. The bonds are insured and triple-A-rated.
                                                                                                       

