<IN>
ECONOMIC NEWS (ECO)
</IN>
<LP>
   Massachusetts Lt. Gov. Evelyn Murphy threatened this week
to seize control of the state's beleaguered finances and
impose her own plan if Gov. Dukakis left on a trade mission.
Considering all the water that's gone over this dam, we loved
the incredible comment of Dukakis ally L. Edward Lashman, who
said Ms. Murphy "is dangerously flirting with the economic
health of the commonwealth of Massachusetts. That's
irresponsible."
</LP>
