<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<GV>
EXECUTIVE (EXE)
</GV>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- President Bush cleared the way for the
approval of "most favored nation" treatment for imports from
Czechoslovakia, and asked Congress to approve a bilateral
trade agreement with the country.
   The White House announced that the president has decided
to approve a waiver of the so-called Jackson-Vanik
restrictions in the 1974 trade act to permit extension of
U.S. tariff concessions to Czechoslovakian imports.
</LP>
