   Polaroid's venture into China is part of the photographic
equipment concern's long-term growth strategy to expand
instant photography beyond traditional geographic markets. In
the past year, Polaroid opened facilities in the Soviet
Union, India and Finland.
   Initially, Polaroid of Shanghai will assemble Polaroid
Supercolor 635CL instant cameras and package Polaroid 600
Plus instant film. Cameras and film will be marketed to
business and industrial markets, as well as to China's more
than 2,500 street photographers.
